\title{fastclogit: Fast Conditional Logit for Large-Scale Choice Data}
\description{
Memory-efficient conditional logit estimation using Rcpp, designed for large-scale discrete choice models with millions to hundreds of millions of rows. Features include a formula interface with automatic factor expansion, McFadden/Manski sampling correction offsets, clustered sandwich standard errors, collinearity detection, and KHB mediation decomposition (Kohler, Karlson & Holm, 2011). Avoids the model.frame/model.matrix memory duplication that makes survival::clogit() infeasible on large datasets.
